# Nikita Zuev

Fullstack Developer | Front-end Developer | React Developer Novi Sad, Serbia · hoffmanmyst@gmail.com· linkedin.com/in/nshoffman· github.com/nshoffman

## Work Experience

Artezio Jun, 2019 - **Apr, 2020**
Junior JavaScript Developer Nizhny Novgorod, Russia · On-site Projects:
- Genco Shipping– **ERP system for a shipping company.**
JavaScript, Alpha Anywhere, MariaDB, REST API;
- Artezio Academy - **Internal internship management platform.**
JavaScript, React, Redux, Redux-Saga, Formik, Reactstrap, SCSS, JQuery, REST API, Docker; Migrated the internal LMS's client-side codebase from Django + JQuery to React; Built custom UI components for the shipping company's ERP system based on wireframes;

## Education

Higher School of Economics Jun, 2019 BS, Major: General and Strategic Management, Minor: Web Development Russia
 **Coursework:** Web Technologies, Programming Basics, Databases, Web Applications Development, Information Management;
 **Achievements:** Winner Award in students competition in Business Informatics; SKILLS
Programming Languages: TypeScript, JavaScript, UnrealScript, Python, Go, SQL; Technologies: React, Redux, Material UI, GraphQL, Apollo, REST API, Node.js, Nest.js, HTML, CSS, SCSS, CSS-in-JS; Tools: NPM, Yarn, Webpack, Vite, ESLint, Babel, Git, Bash, Docker, PostCSS, Figma, Jira; Communication: Russian - C2, English - C1, Serbian - B1; Trak Services Jan, 2023 - **May, 2024**
Fullstack Developer Birmingham, AL, United States · Remote Projects:
- Clear Verify - **Employment and income verification platform.**
TypeScript, React, React Final Form, Material UI, Emotion, Figma, GraphQL, Apollo, Vite, Node.js, 8base API, Sheet.js, yup;
- HR Logics - **Compliance management and profitability solutions.**
TypeScript, React, Material UI, GraphQL, Apollo, Vite, Emotion, Python, AWS, boto3, Nest.js, PostgreSQL, Docker; Built a scalable validation service for data processing module **decreasing overall complexity of validation-related tasks by over 50%**;
 Increased application's backend capabilities to handle 6-10 times larger user data input files; Contributed to development of server-side GraphQL and REST endpoints; Found and eliminated numerous client-side and server-side bugs in critical parts of applications; 8base Mar, 2021 - **Jul, 2022**
Fullstack Developer Saint Petersburg, Russia · Remote Projects:
- Bigfoot Capital –**Business loan and funding platform.**
TypeScript, React, React Final Form, Material UI, Styled Components, GraphQL, Apollo, Node.js, 8base API, MySQL, ramda, xlsx;
- 8base - **Low-code fullstack development SaaS platform.**
TypeScript, React, Redux, Reselect, Redux-Saga, Formik, Material UI, Emotion, Figma, 8base API, Uploadcare; Played a key role in taking the project with major sections unready to the release on time in 3 months; **Ensured expected behavior of the core functionality** involved in calculation of over 80 clients' financial metrics as well as implemented report generation and export logic;
 **Solely built a rich custom Material UI theme** for the platform based on the project's design system; **Developed a complex checkout section** which required filling in of a multistep form with custom user-defined questions; As a member of the core team, contributed to development of various sections of a low-code **fullstack platform**: asset management, external libraries integration, application deployment and versioning management;
